---
description: Refactoring discipline for safe agent changes
alwaysApply: true
---

When refactoring:
- Preserve behavior unless the task explicitly asks to change it.
- Make one conceptual change at a time.
- Prefer incremental improvement over full rewrites.
- Keep public exports stable.
- Update tests when behavior changes.
- Do not rename files, exports or APIs without a clear reason.
- After refactoring, run typecheck and relevant tests.
- Explain what changed and what was intentionally left unchanged.

For dedicated refactoring passes, see rule 007 and `.cursor/rules/external/ciembor/refactoring.mini.md`.
For architecture-level refactoring, see `.cursor/rules/external/ciembor/clean-architecture.mini.md`.
